Step 4

   The final setup piece is to send the output of your Lookup Tables into
   Google Analytics. You can use your generic Universal Analytics Page
   View tag that is already set up in Google Tag Manager.
    1. Open your Google Analytics â€˜Page Viewâ€™ tag.
    2. Expand the â€˜More settingsâ€™ menu, then the â€˜Fields to Setâ€™ menu, and
       click â€˜+Add Fieldâ€™.
    3. Enter the following three â€˜Field Namesâ€™ with the values of the
       three corresponding Lookup Tables:
          + campaignSource â€“ {{Lookup â€“ URL â€“ Fragment â€“ Source}}
          + campaignMedium â€“ {{Lookup â€“ URL â€“ Fragment â€“ Medium}}
          + campaignName â€“ {{Lookup â€“ URL â€“ Fragment â€“ Campaign Name}}

   The values will now be sent to Google Analytics just as if you were
   using the UTM parameters: utm_source, utm_medium and utm_campaign.
